cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SI, cs.MM

The paper discusses the design challenges of mmWave networks in urban regions, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the analysis of connectivity probability, which is related to information theory, leading to the possibility of cs.IT (Information Theory) as the second likely category. The use of random lattice and stochastic geometry theories suggests the possibility of cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the third and fourth likely categories. Finally, the paper focuses on mmWave communication, which is a topic related to multimedia and image processing, leading to the possibility of cs.MM (Multimedia) as the fifth likely category.
